abstract: Ricky Strauss, a successful marketer, has been given oversight of original films and TV shows for Disney’s coming streaming service. Does he have what it takes?
snippet: Ricky Strauss, a successful marketer, has been given oversight of original films and TV shows for Disney’s coming streaming service. Does he have what it takes?
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Very little is known about Disneyflix, as some people in Hollywood are calling the Netflix-style streaming service that Disney plans to introduce late next year.

abstract: A trendy maneuver allows wealthy donors to reap immediate tax benefits, while charities can wait for funds indefinitely — or even forever.

lead_paragraph: Late in 2014, Nicholas Woodman, the founder and chief executive of GoPro, announced what appeared to be an extraordinary act of generosity.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: The Trouble With a $1 Trillion Apple

abstract: High-level meetings, powerful lobbying firms and a charm offensive were unable to get regulators to approve a deal with SkyBridge Capital, Anthony Scaramucci’s firm.
snippet: High-level meetings, powerful lobbying firms and a charm offensive were unable to get regulators to approve a deal with SkyBridge Capital, Anthony Scaramucci’s firm.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Just over a year ago, two senior executives from the giant Chinese conglomerate HNA landed a meeting with Steven Mnuchin, the United States Treasury secretary, at his office. The executives, Adam Tan and Guang Yang, snapped a photo with Mr. Mnuchin, holding a model plane of the HNA-owned carrier, Hainan Airlines.

abstract: In 1977, New York State made carrying small amounts of marijuana in someone’s pocket a ticket-worthy violation, not a crime. But arrests soon skyrocketed.
snippet: In 1977, New York State made carrying small amounts of marijuana in someone’s pocket a ticket-worthy violation, not a crime. But arrests soon skyrocketed.
lead_paragraph: It was the 1970s, and marijuana raids and mass arrests had been sweeping college campuses and suburban concert venues in New York. The crackdown outraged parents. There was talk of ruined reputations and “Gestapo” police tactics.

headline_main: It Wasn’t a Crime to Carry Marijuana. Until the Police Found a Loophole.
headline_print_headline: Officials Made a Successful Attempt to Decriminalize Marijuana. In 1977.

abstract: Mr. Cuomo is likely to be sitting on the same ballot line — that of the Independence Party — with the very Republicans he has called traitors.
snippet: Mr. Cuomo is likely to be sitting on the same ballot line — that of the Independence Party — with the very Republicans he has called traitors.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY — Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo is the de facto leader of the New York State Democratic Party. His formal nomination for a third term came with splashy endorsements from party leaders like Hillary Clinton and Joe Biden. For months, he has rallied and railed against Republicans in Congress, calling them traitors and derelict in their duties.

headline_main: Third-Party Line Will Feature Governor Cuomo, and a Slew of Republicans
headline_print_headline: In November, a Party-Line Vote Could Check a Box for Cuomo and the G.O.P.

abstract: The actress-turned-candidate for governor is trying to persuade skeptical New York Democrats to see beyond her political inexperience, as some did with Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez.
snippet: The actress-turned-candidate for governor is trying to persuade skeptical New York Democrats to see beyond her political inexperience, as some did with Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez.
lead_paragraph: Even then, no one was quite sure what to make of Cynthia Nixon.

headline_main: Cynthia Nixon Thinks You’re Underestimating Her
headline_print_headline: Outgunned, 30 Points Down But Running Like a Favorite

abstract: Some loyal supporters on the left say that Mayor Bill de Blasio has fallen short on fully delivering on several progressive issues.
snippet: Some loyal supporters on the left say that Mayor Bill de Blasio has fallen short on fully delivering on several progressive issues.
lead_paragraph: In his first inaugural address in 2014, Mayor Bill de Blasio invoked the names of legendary reformers, from Fiorello La Guardia to Franklin and Eleanor Roosevelt, and said that in their honor and spirit, he would “commit to a new progressive direction in New York.”

headline_print_headline: Progressives Who Once Hailed De Blasio Bemoan Slow Gains

abstract: Congressman, assemblyman, Staten Island borough president: Even more, he was a Republican kingpin with wide reach in a largely Democratic city.
snippet: Congressman, assemblyman, Staten Island borough president: Even more, he was a Republican kingpin with wide reach in a largely Democratic city.
lead_paragraph: Guy V. Molinari, the longtime Republican kingpin of Staten Island who represented New York City’s least populous, most conservative county as an assemblyman, congressman, borough president and political paterfamilias, died on Wednesday in a Manhattan hospital. He was 89 and had been a lifelong resident of the island.
